    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-23T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-23T16:00:00-05:00" n="354"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">835.796/148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Tuck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Buenos Aires</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-23T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 23, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>756. Local press announces that Condor Airline<note n="31" xml:id="d354fn1"
                        >Sindicato Condor Ltda., nominally a Brazilian company.</note> will
                    inaugurate second weekly service between Buenos Aires and Santiago beginning
                    July 24. Westbound schedules Mondays and Thursdays; eastbound Wednesdays and
                    Saturdays all will stop at Mendoza.</p>
                <p>Panagra<note n="32" xml:id="d354fn2">Pan American-Grace Airways. 1</note> has
                    also been anxious to add another service to Santiago but has been handicapped by
                    scarcity of planes and pilots.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Tuck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
